      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "NIH is established as the primary clinical surrogate for hemolysis; direct mapping from CFD scalar output to NIH must be validated against clinical reference data.",
      "rationale": "NIH is the accepted clinical QoI and the power-law model maps directly to NIH. However, the mapping has not been validated against patient-derived clinical reference data; only in-vitro surrogates available. Achieved level 3 against required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
